1. It allows storing multiple values in a single variable
2. An array is a collection of elements of the same type stored in a Contiguous memory location

   eg; Array namely marks is storing marks of 10 students
       type variable_name [] = {}
       int marks[] = {50, 34, 67, 85, 67, 96, 46, 96, 64, 56}

       marks ->  Array name
       int   ->  Array will be storing integer values
       []    ->  Symbol of array
       {}    ->  values of the integers


3. Characteristics of an Array
      i) Fixed size  ( in above case size of array is 10)
     ii) Size -> no of elements an array can store
    iii) Index-based
     iv) starting index = 0, endIndex = size -1 eg 9  marks[10] will be out of bound
      V) Homogenous elements -> same type of elements
     vi) Contiguous memory location -> all elements will be stored next to each other

4. Types of array
    i) 1D Array:
       Data stored in a single line
       Declare and Initilise values:          int marks[] = { 10, 20, 30, 40}



   ii) 2D Array
  iii) Multi-dimentional array

